@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Music.UI

@*
    Help content for the Music module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Music lets you browse, play, and manage your music library directly from your browser. Stream your personal music collection anywhere.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Browsing Your Library</h2>
        <p>Browse your music by <strong>Albums</strong>, <strong>Artists</strong>, or <strong>Genres</strong> using the sidebar navigation. The library view shows album artwork, artist names, and track listings.</p>
        <p>Use the <strong>search bar</strong> to find specific songs, albums, or artists.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Playback</h2>
        <p>Click a song to play it. The playback controls at the bottom provide play/pause, previous/next track, volume control, and progress bar.</p>
        <p><strong>Now playing:</strong> View the current track details including album art, artist, and progress.</p>
        <p><strong>Shuffle and repeat:</strong> Toggle shuffle mode for random playback or repeat for continuous listening.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Playlists</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating playlists:</strong> Click <strong>New Playlist</strong>, give it a name, and add songs from your library.</p>
        <p><strong>Editing:</strong> Rename, reorder, or delete playlists. Remove individual tracks as needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Favorites</h2>
        <p>Heart songs to add them to your Favorites playlist for quick access.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use playlists to create mood-based or genre-specific listening sessions.</li>
            <li>Favorites are a quick way to access your most-played tracks.</li>
            <li>Search across your entire library to find songs instantly.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
